question: The "Mount Ramelau" is located in which country?
explanation: Mount Ramelau, also known as Tatamailau, is located in the island country of East Timor(Timor-Leste) in the Lesser Sunda Islands of the Malay Archipelago. This mountain is the highest mountain of East Timor and Timor Island. It is 2986 metres high above sea level. BirdLife International identified this area as an Important Bird Area. This mountain is covered with old-growth montane forest.
